Panache			KEY:Panache ~ Swashbuckler		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SwashbucklerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary						DEFINE:SwashbucklerPanachePoints|MAX(1,CHA)	DEFINE:PanachePoints|SwashbucklerPanachePoints	DEFINE:SwashbucklerPanacheMax|CHA	DEFINE:PanacheMax|SwashbucklerPanacheMax	DESC:More than just a lightly armored warrior, you are a daring combatant. You fight with panache: a fluctuating measure of your ability to perform amazing actions in combat. At the start of each day, you gain %1 panache points. Your panache goes up or down throughout the day, but usually cannot go higher than %2, though feats and magic items can affect this maximum. You spend panache to accomplish deeds, and regain panache in the following ways.	DESC:&nl;Critical Hit with a Light or One-Handed Piercing Weapon: Each time you confirm a critical hit with a light or one-handed piercing weapon while in combat, you regain 1 panache point. Confirming a critical hit on a helpless or unaware creature or on a creature that has less than %3 Hit Dice doesn't restore panache.&nl;Killing Blow with a Light or One-Handed Piercing Weapon: When you reduce a creature to 0 or fewer hit points with a light or one-handed piercing weapon attack while in combat, you regain 1 panache point. Destroying an unattended object, reducing a helpless or unaware creature to 0 or fewer hit points, or reducing a creature that has less than %3 Hit Dice to 0 or fewer hit points doesn't restore any panache.|PanachePoints|PanacheMax|floor(TL/2)|PREVARGT:TL,3	DESC:&nl;Critical Hit with a Light or One-Handed Piercing Weapon: Each time you confirm a critical hit with a light or one-handed piercing weapon while in combat, you regain 1 panache point. Confirming a critical hit on a helpless or unaware creature doesn't restore panache.&nl;Killing Blow with a Light or One-Handed Piercing Weapon: When you reduce a creature to 0 or fewer hit points with a light or one-handed piercing weapon attack while in combat, you regain 1 panache point. Destroying an unattended object, reducing a helpless or unaware creature to 0 or fewer hit points doesn't restore any panache.|PanachePoints|PanacheMax|PREVARLTEQ:TL,3																										SOURCEPAGE:p.44	ASPECT:CheckCount|%1|PanacheMax	ASPECT:CheckType|Points per Day
Deeds				KEY:Deeds ~ Swashbuckler		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SwashbucklerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality								DEFINE:DeedsLVL|SwashbucklerLVL																								DESC:You spend panache points to accomplish deeds. Most deeds grant you a monetary bonus or effect, but some provide longer-lasting effects. Some deeds remain in effect as long as you have at least 1 panache point. Unless otherwise noted, a deed can be performed multiple successive times, as long as you have or spend the required number of panache points to perform the deed.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.45	ASPECT:MasterAbility|Deeds
Swashbuckler Finesse	KEY:Finesse ~ Swashbuckler		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SwashbucklerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality			SERVESAS:FEAT|Weapon Finesse																														DESC:You gain the benefits of the Weapon Finesse feat with light or one-handed piercing melee weapons, and you can use your Charisma score in place of Intelligence as a prerequisite for Combat Expertise. This ability counts as having the Weapon Finesse feat for purposes of meeting feat prerequisites.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT.Piercing|((max(STR,DEX)-STR)+SHIELDACCHECK)|TYPE=NotRanged													SOURCEPAGE:p.46
Charmed Life		KEY:Charmed Life ~ Swashbuckler	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SwashbucklerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary						DEFINE:CharmedLifeTimes|0																									DESC:You have a knack for getting out of trouble. %1 times per day, as an immediate action before attempting a saving throw, you can add your Charisma bonus to the result of the save. You must choose to do this before the roll is made, and may only apply one use of charmed life on a given save.|CharmedLifeTimes																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|CharmedLifeTimes|3+floor((SwashbucklerLVL-2)/4)			SOURCEPAGE:p.46	ASPECT:CheckCount|%1|CharmedLifeTimes	ASPECT:CheckType|Uses per Day
Nimble			KEY:Nimble ~ Swashbuckler		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SwashbucklerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary						DEFINE:SwashbucklerNimbleBonus|0																								DESC:You gain a +%1 dodge bonus to AC while wearing light or no armor. Anything that causes you to lose your Dexterity bonus to AC also causes you to lose this dodge bonus.|SwashbucklerNimbleBonus																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:COMBAT|AC|SwashbucklerNimbleBonus|TYPE=Dodge					BONUS:VAR|SwashbucklerNimbleBonus|min(floor((SwashbucklerLVL+1)/4),5)	SOURCEPAGE:p.47

