# Ability Name			Unique Key							Category of Ability		Type											Description																																																																																																																																																																															Source Page		Aspects
Derring-Do				KEY:Derring-Do ~ Swashbuckler				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.DeedsLVL1.DeedsHasPanacheCost.Extraordinary	DESC:You can spend 1 panache point when you make an Acrobatics, Climb, Escape Artist, Fly, Ride, Swim check to roll d6 and add the result to the check. You must choose to do this before you roll. If the d6 roll is a natural "6," you roll another d6 and add it to the check.	DESC:You can continue to do this as long as you roll natural "6s" up to a number %1 times.|DEX|PREVARGTEQ:DEX,2																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.45	ASPECT:ChildAbility|Deeds
Dodging Panache			KEY:Dodging Panache ~ Swashbuckler			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.DeedsLVL1.DeedsHasPanacheCost.Extraordinary	DESC:When an opponent attempts a melee attack against you, you can spend 1 panache point to move 5 feet as an immediate action; doing so grants you a +%1 bonus to AC against the triggering attack. This movement doesn't negate the attack, which is still resolved as if you were in the original square. This movement is not a 5-foot step; it provokes attacks of opportunity from creatures other than the one who triggered this deed. You can only perform this deed while wearing light or no armor, and while carrying no more than a light load.|CHA																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.45	ASPECT:ChildAbility|Deeds
Opportune Parry and Riposte	KEY:Opportune Parry and Riposte ~ Swashbuckler	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.DeedsLVL1.DeedsHasPanacheCost.Extraordinary	DESC:When an opponent makes a melee attack against you, you can spend 1 panache point and can expend a use of an attack of opportunity to attempt to parry that attack. You make an attack roll as if you were making an attack of opportunity. If your attack roll is greater than the roll of the attacking creature, the attack automatically misses. For each size category the attacking creature is larger than you, you take a -2 penalty on your attack roll. You must declare the use of this ability after the creature's attack is announced, but before that attack roll is made. Immediately after you perform a successful parry, as long as you have 1 panache point you can make an attack as an immediate action against the creature whose attack you blocked, provided that creature is within your reach.																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.45	ASPECT:ChildAbility|Deeds
# 3rd Level
Kip-Up				KEY:Kip-Up ~ Swashbuckler				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.DeedsLVL3.Extraordinary				DESC:As long as you have at least 1 panache point, you can kip-up from prone as a move action without provoking an attack of opportunity. If she spends 1 panache point when she kips up, she can do this as a swift action instead.																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.45	ASPECT:ChildAbility|Deeds
Menacing Swordplay		KEY:Menacing Swordplay ~ Swashbuckler		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.DeedsLVL3.Extraordinary				DESC:While you have at least 1 panache point, when you hit an opponent with a light or one-handed piercing melee weapon, you can choose to use Intimidate to demoralize that opponent as a swift action instead of a standard action.																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.45	ASPECT:ChildAbility|Deeds
Precise Strike			KEY:Precise Strike ~ Swashbuckler			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.DeedsLVL3.Extraordinary				DESC:As long as you have at least 1 panache point, you gain the ability to strike precisely with a light or one-handed piercing melee weapon (though not natural weapon attacks), adding +%1 to your damage roll. To use this deed, you cannot attack with a weapon in your other hand or use a shield other than a buckler. You can even use this ability with thrown light or one-handed piercing weapons, as long as the target is within 30 feet. Any creature that is immune to sneak attacks is immune to a precise strike, and any item or ability that protects a creature from critical hits also protects a creature from a precise strike. The extra damage of precise strike is precision damage, and isn't multiplied with a critical hit.<br/>As a swift action, you can spend 1 panache point to double your precise strike's damage bonus on the next attack. This must be used before the end of your turn, or it is lost. This deed's cost cannot be reduced any ability or effect that reduces the amount of panache points a deed costs (such as the Signature Deed feat).	SOURCEPAGE:p.45	ASPECT:ChildAbility|Deeds
Swashbuckler Initiative		KEY:Swashbuckler Initiative ~ Swashbuckler	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.DeedsLVL3.Extraordinary				DESC:While you have at least 1 panache point, your gain a +2 bonus on initiative checks. In addition, if you have the Quick Draw feat, your hands are free and unrestrained, and your weapon isn't hidden, your can draw a single light or one-handed piercing weapon as part of the initiative check.																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.45	ASPECT:ChildAbility|Deeds

